HEADWORD: Fragor
<hw>Fra"gor</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a breaking
to pieces, fr. <ets>frangere</ets> to break.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
loud and sudden sound; the report of anything bursting; a crash.</def>
<rj><au>I. Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <note>[Due to confusion with <xex>fragrant</xex>.]</note>
<def>A strong or sweet scent.</def> <mark>[Obs. & Illegitimate.]</mark>
<rj><au>Sir T. Herbert.</au></rj></p>

<p><ent>Fragrancy</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Fragrance</ent>⟦br⟧
